Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees (middle and top positions for 4 servings). Wash and dry produce.

Peel and slice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Vegetables ==

Heat a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Toss sweet potato, zucchini, bell pepper, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} (for 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks). Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Salmon ==

Pat @salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon to pan, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Flip and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from pan and set aside.

== Miso Maple Glaze ==

Heat same pan over medium-high heat. Add @miso sauce concentrate{1}, @maple syrup{2%tbsp}, ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and half the sesame seeds. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide sweet potato jumble, rice, and salmon between plates. Garnish rice with remaining sesame seeds. Spoon glaze over salmon; drizzle any remaining over jumble and serve.